      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope (flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties) with documented uncertainty on all boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "Four of five target operating points are represented in experimental data. Fluid temperature control uncertainty is documented. One high-flow operating point has no matching experimental condition, creating a gap at the boundary of the COU envelope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (e.g., E_avg, NRMSE) with uncertainty bounds on both simulation and experiment; metric must meet pre-specified acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error on hemolysis index is 34% across four operating points, exceeding the pre-specified 15% threshold. Experimental measurement uncertainty is documented but simulation uncertainty intervals are wide due to model-form uncertainty in the power-law hemolysis model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
