      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest used in validation (hemolysis index, wall shear stress) must directly correspond to clinical decision quantities.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary clinical decision quantity and is directly computed and compared. Wall shear stress distributions are used as intermediate validation quantities. QoI relevance is adequate at the required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use patient-representative blood analog, pump geometry identical to COU device, and operating conditions spanning the full COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation used a glycerol-water blood analog rather than porcine blood; viscosity is matched but viscoelastic effects are not captured. Pump geometry is the FDA generic model, not the sponsor's proprietary impeller. These representativeness gaps reduce achieved level to 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
