      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review of simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing steps by an independent analyst.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. A single analyst configured and post-processed all cases. Use-error risk is unquantified; factor not-assessed at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of turbulence model selection and power-law hemolysis model coefficients with sensitivity analysis across plausible model-form alternatives.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected without comparative evaluation against alternative turbulence closures. Power-law hemolysis model coefficients taken from literature without recalibration to the FDA pump geometry. Model-form uncertainty is the dominant source of prediction error but is not formally assessed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Probability distributions assigned to all uncertain model inputs (viscosity, density, inlet velocity profile, rotational speed) with Monte Carlo propagation through the hemolysis model.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed but only rotational speed and inlet flow rate were treated as uncertain inputs. Blood viscosity variability and inlet velocity profile uncertainty were held fixed at nominal values. Input uncertainty is undercharacterized."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sufficient experimental replicates (n ≥ 5 per operating point) with statistical characterization of inter-sample variability in hemolysis measurements.",
      "rationale": "Experimental dataset contains n=3 replicates per operating point. Statistical power is insufficient to characterize tail-end hemolysis variability relevant to worst-case patient exposure. Factor not-assessed due to inadequate sample size."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
